Insurance companies face data sprawl with disparate systems and¬error-prone manual processes impeding a holistic view of the business and risk exposure. Gaining this insight is critical at a time when the regulatory environment demands businesses improve their risk models and practices.

Using actuarial statistical analysis and modelling based upon Microsoft solutions, insurance companies are able to better identify risks, price¬policies more effectively, understand their liabilities more accurately,¬and optimise their financial positions.

As the pace of global financial services accelerates and speed becomes essential to decision-making, traditional tools are simply too slow. Coupled with massive on-premises server farms being unsustainably expensive, there is a real need for higher computing throughput but with a compelling TCO.

Microsoft analytics solutions enable financial institutions to benefit from cloud computing by reducing capex and facilitating more complex data analysis. Typical scenarios include risk computation and modelling plus predictive analytics through machine learning of data analysis & patterns.

Faced with exponentially increasing volumes of data, it is challenging for financial institutions to translate that data into insight needed to improve customer profitability and retention. To do this effectively, you need deeper insight into the profitability of you customer portfolio and have the ability to visualise that data so it is actionable.

With Microsoft customer and product analytics solutions, you can capitalise on internal and external data to combine profitability, segmentation and customer preference, to gain a complete end-to-end view of the customer.

Through integration with its familiar Office and BI tools, Microsoft offers customers powerful data visualisations to gain insights on all their structured and unstructured data.

Unlike the competition, Microsoft enables customers to make breakthrough discoveries by boosting their data and models with publicly available data and services from several sources, including social media sites like Twitter and Facebook. Thanks to applications and mining algorithms on Windows Azure Marketplace, customers can uncover hidden patterns in their data.

Microsoft enables customers to realise the benefits of Big Data through a modern data management platform that seamlessly handles data of all types (including structured, unstructured, and real-time data) and scale. We bring the simplicity of Windows to Hadoop, extend your data warehouse with Hadoop, and offer the elastic scale of the cloud to Big Data.

The Microsoft business insight solution provides marketing, product, and operations teams with a comprehensive set of advanced analytics which are easy to generate and use, and help in creating more value from customer and market insights.

The frequency of customer interactions with CSPs are increasing. As a result, mining greater volumes and a larger variety of data will become a powerful competitive asset. Microsoft big data solutions help with customer segmentation and analysis of customer loyalty and sentiment.

Sentiment analytics can be used to gauge customer satisfaction, allowing the service provider to proactively reach out to dissatisfied users, thus increasing customer loyally and reducing churn. Data streaming approaches with technologies like StreamInsight can dramatically improve fraud detection by analysing near real-time data windows without the need for long term storage.

Pattern matching and network telemetry can help pinpoint troublesome issues with network quality of customer equipment, allowing the operator to react more rapidly to potential problems—and thus improving overall quality of service and customer satisfaction.

The Microsoft billing and CRM solutions provide valuable analytics and reporting tools with real-time visibility into what subscribers are doing on an operator’s network—how services and products are being used and consumed, and which promotions, products, and services are most popular amongst various customer segments, and how many movies or mobile games subscribers purchased.

¬The solutions enable a full suite of order management capabilities, including workflows to manage complex activation ordering, physical installations, equipment reservations and allocations, fault resolutions, technical dispatch, and on-site installations. Order management also enables offline credit checks and facilities confirmations.

Because Microsoft Dynamics CRM is fully integrated into partners’ BSS platform, keeping pace with the constant introduction of new technologies becomes much simpler. This helps operators to future-proof their CRM, potentially saving millions in customisation charges over time and simplifying the CRM desktop by linking all back office systems,  streamlining business data for more accurate, consistent, and agile operations.

A solid and reliable BSS platform is a critical component for every service provider. Microsoft and its partners are experienced, long-standing vendors in the telecommunications industry. By pairing Microsoft’s strengths in CRM technology and usability with partners’ strengths in billing and CRM projects, we have created a world-class product that is greater than the sum of its parts.

The billing and CRM solutions are much more than a customer care solution. They drive value across the entire organisation for groups such as marketing, finance, sales, product management, and networks. They automate business processes, including order management, workflow automation, and contract management, for an end-to-end view of the full customer life cycle.
